(11, 5, '11. The ships had their days of …………………. in the 1840s and 1850s.', 'a. glorious', 'b. glory', 'c. glorify', 'd. gloriously', 'B'),
(12, 5, '12. Tea loses its flavor quickly …………………… in the hold of a vessel.', 'a. when storing', 'b. stored', 'c. when stored', 'd. to paint', 'D'),
(13, 5, '14. The crime rate has continued to rise in American cities despite efforts on the part of both\r\ngovernment and private citizens to curb ................', 'a. them', 'b. him', 'c. its', 'd. it', 'D'),
